Diana: An Ancient Ritual
Sat Mar 20 03:21:56 2004
To: kot undead immortal
A lone figure, weak and thin, walked through the forest. All around her, animals were quiet, the trees themselves seemed to cower from the intruder. It was not the power they feared, it was the intent. Animals can sense something when it is about to happen, like the swine before the Cataclysm.
The figure walked into a glade. The glade was barren, empty, no sound or animal, no breeze or smell, save for one thing. In the center was a corpse, head thrown back in agony. In its ribcage was.. something. It was a sphere. It was not black or dark, it was simply... nothing.
The figure walked forward and pulled off its hood, revealing  pale white skin and colorless hair. The whole figure was devoid of color, save for two brilliant blue eyes, which slowly worked their way over the skeleton before them.
"{DHello Diana. It is a pleasure to look upon your body once more.. what is this? Did you fear I would not keep my promise? That I would not hold to a pact I made at your birth?{x"
Diana raised her head slightly. The voice came from within her, and she knew it, she had heard it before, she had heard it everyday since the day she was born. "{bYes... I was worried. But now I am not, I fear nothing..{x"
"{DExcellent, I see that we were not wrong in choosing each other. Need I even tell you what to do? I know you have known the deeds you will do today whilst still in your mothers womb.{x"
Diana cringed slightly at those words. "{bDo not mock me.. I was not born of a woman... my mother... was not a woman.{x"
"{DHow true, how true... you are right... do you know what you see before you? Or can you hear my voice before I even speak it, like your mother could?{x"
Diana knew. "{bI will do it... I will see you soon.{x" Diana pulled off her tattered robes and stood naked in the center of the grove. She looked down and, though it had not been there a second before, saw a simple rusted dagger in the corpses hand. Diana took that and held it in her right hand, sweat pouring from her whole body.
She let out one last breath, and put the point of the dagger to her sternum. Slowly, the point bit deep, spilling {Rblood{x on the ground at her feet. She slowly brought the knife down her torso, stopping just below her navel.
Diana did not gasp in pain, no... in fact, with each inch of skin that was ripped asunder, her face grew more and more calm. When she was done with the dagger, she dropped it, watching it slowly slide out of her flesh and land in the pool of blood at her feet.
Diana began speaking. It was no language any on krynn had heard. It was a half gurgle, half pant... no, it was nothing but the language of magic, warped by the damaged lungs and heart.
Finally, the grove returned to silence. There was a flash of... darkness, and Diana had thought the ritual over. But when her vision returned, she looked down at the corpse of her mother. The sphere had lifted off the ground, and now floated slowly along the spinal column, through the pelvis and up to Diana.
Diana looked at it, and it seemed to look back at her, and then, as if they had both reached an agreement, it lept into the open wound in her chest. Diana, her strength returning despite her loss of blood, reached into the hole and grabbed something. Out came a heart, no longer beating, yet she felt a pulse. The orb within her beat as her heart had beaten earlier. She dropped her heart on the ground and closed her eyes in ecstacy as the wound closed up, leaving no trace of previous events.
"{D*laugh* Yes Diana, our dreams are come true... yours which you have had for less then half a century, mine which I have had since before Paladine created the elves.{x" This time, the voice did not come from her head.. it came from her chest.
"{bYes, let your will be done first, and then mine.{x"
Diana took a deep breath, her first since the ritual began. She picked up her robes and slid back into them, then walked quickly and forcefully out of the glade...

~
