Subject Talmate: Sanity~
Text
I was on my way home after the long journey from Neraka to Palanthas. To say the least I was in good sprits, but would not be for long I was soon to discover. It had not taken long for me to get back home from Planthas, because I had used the ways a magic to get there and back. I stood at my front door in that small alley in a matter of seconds. I dont know why but I paused before I entered, it was just for that split second, but some how deep inside I knew that it might bee my last moment of sanity.
 
 
  I entered the small house and to my suprise my father was sitting by himself, in our little living room. He was doing one thing I had never seen him do, he was crying. 'Where is mother' I asked him in a worried tone. 'S..she is i..in her be...bed' He had said between sobs. 'Pl...please do not go to h...her she i...is sleeping her enter...enternal rest.'
 
 
  For the first time in my life I had been scared. I may be a dark person, but my parents were everything to me so when I heard my father speek these word I had broke. I ran to her, she lie motionless in her bed. I began to shake her vielently, 'wake up, wake up mother' I cried but she would not move. I fell to the floor in pain, the pain of loss.
 
 
  My father eventuly came to the room. He walked to me, I lie broken on the floor. He lifted me of the floor into his arms and carried me off to my room. On the way there I looked into his eyes, they we the blackest of pits. He layed me on my bed and turned to leave before he shut the door he turned and said 'Good bye son, sleep well and know that your mother and I will always be with you', he left me to cry.
 
 
  I eventuly fell victem to sleep to wake in the morning to a slient house. I stood up and ran to their room. All was the same as the day before. My mother lay on her side of the bed dead. One thing had changed though, now my father lay next to her a dagger sticking out of his heart. My mind shattered, at any point it would break. I slumped to the floor and lay there for a long time.
~
