Subject Jeslek's history~
Text
On the coast lands, near the bay of ballfor, nearly 250 years ago, on the
night the two moons lit the sky, and the third moon was said to grace the
sky as well unseen to all but some.  A stiffled cry was sent out into the
silent night.  The midwife sat there wrapping the newborn son in the warmest
of blankets.  Gently cleaning the babes face and pacing around the bed to
lay him with his mother.  Turning "I will go and fetch some water" Closing
that door on another miracle she had attended.  These times by herself after
her job was done was always the hardest on her.  She found herself getting
eatin alive from the inside.  The knowledge of never being able to have a
child of her own was what made her choose her profession.  If she could not
have children then she was going to make sure others had there healthy
babes.  She was the best, and she was getting older, the only human in the
city she found herself jealous of there long lived life's.  How casually
they took life in a land filled with elves where childbirth was not that
common, .  And to have a child born with all three moons present!  Something
was different about this night.  Every other child she had walked away from
without a thought, but she couldn't let it go.  It was her turn to be a
mother.  So what if the child happened to be an elf!  She would raise the
child in her image her beliefs she had so much to teach so much to pass on
and no one to love.  She wiped her eyes before coming back into the house
with the water she had promised to find the father gone on an errand and the
mother sleeping soundly, her newborn babe nestled in a comfortable crook of
her arm.  The woman glanced about nervously her consciousness gnawing at her
insides.  Now is the time you'll never get an opportunity like this again! 
She reached in to grab the child, when the mothers eyes popped open.  Not
flinching in the slightest the lady whispered a few arcane words and a black
shadow of a hand reached out from the bed and clamped across the mothers
face suffocating her and trying to pull her through the bed.  And a toss of
a powder she vanished in a cloud of mist.  That night there were two wails
on the silent crisp air.  Living the life of solitude was something he came
to enjoy, yet something seemed to be missing for him.  The essence of life
just did not seem complete it followed him throughout his first years of
life.  Growing up not knowing his father but being told of his sea elven
father and heritage.  Not sure where his father had come from or even what
his name was his human mother Grailis had taught him everything he knew. 
She was a kind woman and had taken good care of him his entire life.  She
was an accomplished dabbler in the magic's, all self taught but with stern
beliefs of the right and wrong ways to handle magic.  She taught him the
basics of magic and found he had quite a talent for it.  Over the next 10
years she taught him everything she had learned.  Perhaps if he had stayed
with his elven parents his teachings would have been spread out through a
century, but in the short lifespan of a human things aren't that simple they
don't have the luxury of time.  Soon he came to find out exactly how frail
life truly was when the only woman he had ever loved lay on her deathbed. 
As she lay there looking up at her son her beautiful miracle child she
beckoned for him to come closer and wheezed out the one thing she had not
shared with him.  "I love you my son, There is something I have kept from
you your father his name your true moth."  The life fleeing fom her ragged
body taking her secret to the grave.  He buried her in her favorite spot for
sitting where you could smell the fields and hear the sounds of nature under
an old willow tree.  He took out his knife and carved in the trunk here lies
a loving mother may the three moons watch over her.  He left that same night
and never turned back not knowing where to go.  He had heard much of the
lands about him and he was in search for another tutor to widen his
abilities.  And in the back of his mind sitting there knawing at him What
did she mean a secret?  What about my father.  And the biggest mystery my
moth?  One foot in front of another running through his memories the
troubled youth walked the realms a young man in search of the tower of high
sorcery.  His mother had told him of it had described to him had even
created illusions of the place.  Only the finest mage's in the land were
accepted, and he was determined to be among them.
~
