I sigh.  The barkeep slaps me across the head with his ragged cloth, muttering something about my presence.  I snarl at him and reaching into my pouch, toss my last four steel coins on the counter.  He sends me a look, that look that says, 'You still owe me two-hundred more for all you've done!  Once you're paid, you're out!' 
What makes him think I'll pay now?
Shaking my head I brush my beardless chin and wonder how the Mercenaries are doing, and wondering how long I can rely on them?  I know that the nobles in every city I've visited has the steel to keep me providing the Mercenaries, but how long will they keep taking my steel?  As long as they can help me provoke the war between the Solamnic Knights and the Knights of Takhisis.
I quickly down the ale in front of me and close my eyes.  Sure there are some knights I would like to live through the war.  I'm doing this for all mortals, after all, but sacrifices must be made.  If everything goes as planned, I'd be more then willing to make the ultimate sacrifice for the cause.
 
