Subject She Would Die Alone~
Text
Broken was how she was born, and broken was what she forever would be. The wooden planks beneath her soft cheek gave her no comfort in their splintery kiss, her pale robes, once a good representation of everything she wished to become now only showing the world what she had been turned to by no choice of her own.
 
Every name she had ever been called, every cold glance, every brush off now played through her twirling thoughts as she vainly tried to push herself away from the loving ground, but such efforts were wasted for this would be her final rest.
 
She'd survived her nightmare filled childhood of sickness and hatred, survived the remarks, the scorn she received upon her "recovery," and stumbled her way through her unofficial exhilement despite her having turned not to the dark gods.
 
She'd left everyone she'd ever cared for or loved behind just so they would be happy, they no longer having to be seen alongside one who had come, according to them, under some foul curse of the dark gods; and so she came to Palanthas, seeking sanctuary in the one thing that had never failed her.
 
Frail fingers clenched, their hold against one another weakened and barely felt, the effort sending a violent tremble through her frail arms as tears came to sting at her eyes. She was alone, as always, left alone in her final hour to fade away with evenings light. Brilliant blue eyes closed slowly on the world, her tears flowing seemingly freely now as her strength began to ebb, her world shrinking in upon itself as her thoughts began to slowly slip from her clinging grasp..
 
"Silent one," "Speechless apprentice," and all the long winded insults and foul stares she'd ever received for her silence flooded back to her thoughts, threatening to spill over the darkness which was attempting to claim her.
 
She was a mute, it was true, but she'd been blessed in that her magic had not been taken until she'd turned from Solinari in the end. He'd promised her when she was young, that her gift would not be wasted, that while she'd be unable to whisper even a breath her voice in magic wouldn't be quieted by her physical ailment. There was no crutch in his gift, no burst of godly strength, simply the promise that her magic would not wither and die within her
 
Such thoughts began to fade now, only the sound of her own shallow breathing reaching her ears. What little light that was offered from the setting sun was failing now, its warmth trickling from her porcelain skin as it sank beneath the treetops and houses which surrounded her, the shadows spilling into the back alleyway to drown her away in their cold as her last breath came and all was stilll..
 
 
 
 
(OOC: I left this short. No one really bothered all that much to know Vivienne, and so I won't tell you all what you don't wish to know. :P I'd like to thank though, Yerthorn, Dietrich, and Roman (who this story will be forwarded to also since he took the time to roleplay with Vivienne and isn't in this clan I don't think) for making my time here fun (both ICly and OOCly), and giving me an actual reason to log on in the hopes of getting some roleplay.
 
It's been fun, but with the death of my character and countless hours logged in with me doing nothing but sitting - I don't really think I'm cut out for MUD roleplaying, so no hard feelings. Farewell and I apologize for the OOC at the end of this story)
