Diary of an orphan assassin
A small dust covered book reveals itself as you look over the shelves of
books in front of you.  Thin, and full of ramblings of an obviously gnomish
nature.  Your curiosity finally gets the better of you.  Taking a deep
breath, preparing yourself for what is obviously a gnomish story, you
finally brush the dust off and open the book.  My name is Neoa, the acronym
for the name is not important, nore is the name any more.  You know, my
family always said if you are ever in trouble, simply surrender.  Everything
will work out better that way.  The people attacking you, or trying to take
over your land will get information, and eventually you will get a good bit
of knowledge out of the situation.  Failing that, you probably will get the
information you want to know eventually.  After all they dont consider you a
threat, so, after a while, what can it hurt.  My family, if they were alive
today would not be proud to here me write these next words.  They were
wrong.  All through my life I knew I was different.  I was bigger to name
one of quite a few differences.  The good news is, I suppose it does not
matter any more.  Soon I shall escape from here, or die trying.  This
mountain is quite different from where I grew up.  It is colder, darker, and
there are no explosions to keep me asleep.  It is much two quiet.  I have
finished painting the portrait, to the best of my memory, of my family.  It,
along with the weapons, and few devices I have invented will be the only
things that I shall take with me.  When I need strength to do what I need to
do, I will look at the painting of my family, I will draw strength from
there death and not allow it to consume me.  Soon the ones that killed my
family will pay.  They will pay for slaying them in cold blood right in
front of me.  They will pay for imprisoning me.  They will pay for not
believing me when I repeatedly told them the mission my family was on while
we were in that city of what I now realize must contain the vary essence of
evil and hatred itself.  Yes, all of them will pay for taking my life that I
loved so well from me.  But first.  I grow weary of speaking this tongue of
dwarves.  And most of all.  I grow weary of not being free.  First I must
get rid of a slight problem I have with a family of dwarves.  Then my
vengeance against the dark ones can begin.  
~
