After many nights spent in Neraka, deep in both thought, and prayer, I knew what I had to do.. I lead myself to the Stronghold, to the temple, to find just who I needed, Lord Razel. He was there, kneeling before the altar, with his head bowed, a soft mutter leaving his lips, prayers. I simply stood at the entrance, knowing what needed to be said, my mind strong.. guided.
 
"{DLord Razel..{x" I said, the words leaving my lips calmly and quietly; my head still lowered a bit, as I spoke, out of respect for the temple. I slowly lifted my head, and straightened myself, to face Razel fully, and crossed my arms; deeming it necessary. "{DWe need to speak..{x" I forced myself to add, only to specify his reaction more to my liking.
 
Razel unexpectedly stops at the first sound of my voice, though finishes his quiet prayer before slowly rising, and still facing the altar, he bows to it, a gesture of reverence, supposedly, before he faces me. "{DYes, my Lord..?{x" He says, the words evenly spoken, with a humble tone.
 
I exhaled slowly, even deeply, to see the reaction of Razel, to try to show an emotion, even if grief. "{DI have put much thought into this decision,{x" I said, my expression hardening a bit before I continued, "{Dand I have done much planning, to find a solution to any possible problem that could arise..{x" Stating quite plainly, I hoped for a more.. positive reaction.. though I still expected a harsh one.
 
Showing no facial expression, Razel nods slowly, the only response vague, with his eyes staring blankly into mine, as if in thought, of anything.. contemplation, or otherwise.
 
I nodded once, leveled, and measured perfectly, graceful even, as far as a nod goes. Though the odd expression of my own, even if hardly visible, unchanging. "{DI will be stepping down, as Lord of Night, Lord Razel..{x" Razel's interest seemingly perked with such simple words, though he chose to hide it. "{DThe position will be passed down to you; and I will be posted in Neraka.. the Queen wishes for me to revive her armies..{x" I said surely, my tone quite smooth, and convincing.
 
Taking a while for a descent response to formulate, Razel appeared to be quite confused, "{DLord?{x" He asked respectfully, though I'm sure he meant pardon, for lack of better words.. "{DThis is very.. unexpected...{x" Pausing for a few moments before a smile begins to work its way upon his face. "{DI will work with you in any, -any- way you want; and the Queen will flourish above all else.{x" He said, apparently, concealing as much enthusiasm as he could.
 
A slight, involuntary smile of my own began to form on my lips, and I began to nod, as expected. "{DShe shall..{x" The words left my lips slowly, before I continued, "{DI know that you have potential, Lord Razel, which is why I expect everything. Lead well, Razel, and show your might to the Queen.{x" I stated firmly, my eyes carefully drifting to the corner of the room; I could've sworn I felt a presence.
 
"{DExpect several visits from me, Lord.{x" Razel says, his smile broadening, as he extends his hand towards me. "{DIts been a pleasure serving under you, Lord Roivas.{x"
 
Hardly hearing his words, I began to focus on the corner of the temple, and the shadows that shrouded it. I had lost my sense of reality. I knew something was there. I felt it.
 
Seemingly out of the shadows in the corner of which I was focused, a beautiful woman with pale skin and long black hair slowly faded into existence, my eyes slowly widening with each moment, and my expression falling blank.
 
The pale skinned beauty swished her long black hair, and it fell seductively about her face.. I'll never forget the sight.. as she slowly, and gracefully made her way towards the both of us.
 
Razel's hand dropped immediately as my expression was noticed, and he to turned himself around slightly, to cock his head to the side and find what I was seeing himself, though as his eyes fell upon her, his head dropped instantly in reverence.
 
Making her way intricately towards us, she stops in between us both, at which point, my head finally drops, in the near presence of the woman. Paying no mind to me, she turned directly to Razel, and bent over, placing a gentle finger beneath his chin.. Oh, how I envied him.. as she slowly lifted his head, her voice so perfectly lustful, as she whispered "{bStand..{x"
 
Razel, shaking lightly at her touch, even, forces himself to lift his head, and straighten himself; though he is unable to look her in the eye, for whatever reason, his trembling proceeding to worsen as he stands.
 
The pale skinned woman slowly stands straight up, and turns to me, yet my head remained lowered.. I felt like it needed to be, so that I couldn't see her face, instead, my eyes were fixed upon her chest. She then took me with both hands, by my hips, and pulls herself in, close to me, leaned in a bit, and lowered her head; to place her chin just below my shoulder.
She then inhaled deeply.. so deeply.. as she ran her nose, which was lightly pressed against my shoulder, along my neck, and up the side of my face, until it reached my ear.
 
I kept my head lowered.. faced with a combination of honor, awe, and nervousness as she acted. Choosing to simply await further action, I held my stance, firmly, though couldn't help but to bite my bottom lip out of anxiousness..
~
