Her lips almost seemed to nibble at my ear and her whisper sounding like quiet music.. "{bYou have chosen the path which I have always planned for you, the knights will be left for Razel; and you will find glory in Neraka.. I have watched you walk longingly in that place and I bless your path.{x" I simply stood, words unable to reach my lips..
 
She pushed herself away from me after a few silent moments, to turn and face Razel once more. She looked back her and offered me a smile.. which I hardly noticed.. still awestruck.. before she whipped her head around to look at Razel, and she beckoned him towards her single, tempting finger.
 
Razel took the few steps required to close the space between him and the woman, though he does it so quickly.. with such desire.. it would seem as if she drew him near her..
 
The pale woman spoke to Razel, though her voice still quiet, "{bYou will continue to lead my Knights; as Roivas has said, though until the ranks of the Lily swell, there shall be no Lord of Night, no one needs the role, at this point in time..{x" She tilted her head to the side, a playful expression haunting her now. "{bDo you understand my wishes..?{x"
 
"{DI do, my Queen.{x" Razel said, a humble tone finding its way to his voice, as he speaks, then lowering his head, he stands, his entire body still shaking slightly in her presence.

She smiled, before twisting herself around, to face me once more. "{bAre you now ready to continue your path..?{x" She asked, a strange, indescribable tone to her voice.
 
I only nodded once, though it was very firmly. "{DI've always been ready, my Queen.{x" I stated, yet sadly, it was too plain for my liking.
 
She tilts her head to the side once more, her seductive smile growing. "{bI look forward to seeing the shadows of Neraka stirring again..{x" She said quietly, before turning around, and heading for the shadows that she appeared from, a gentle hand placed on Razel's shoulder as she walks by; directly into the shadows disappearing with that, leaving the room silent.
