into a larger town. No one still living in the city today is certain of the year it was
established, but it was a ways before the War of the Lance. During its slow progression, a
wonderful, but small temple was constructed to Majere. It was the only one in the village,
and was a place of worship for many. As word of the completion of the temple spread 
from mouth to mouth, occasionally at first, but becoming more frequent, thieves began to
visit the temple for thier own ill gain. In order to combat this, the citizens of Dart decided
decided that a wall around their town was necessary, and so construction began. The old men of
the city, many whom served as guards in Palanthas, began to train the young men and
boys of the city in hopes of providing a proper defense, which worked for many years.
 
Now this style of life went on for many a year, until one day, at the height of their power,
the Seekers came to pay a visit to the city. Many of the inhabitants were oblivious to the
ongoings throughout the lands, and as such, treated the Seekers as they would anyone
else, and denied them access to the city. This proved to be a costly mistake for the
citizens of Dart, and within a few months time, they noticed a small army at their gate.
Instead of surrendering to the army before them, the men of the city chose to stand their
ground and fight, which subsequently most were killed in the battle.
 
Once the Seekers overwhelmed the forces before them, they proceeded to drive the
monks from the Temple, and left it a hollowed shell compared to what it used to be. The
army drove the inhabitants from the city, except the young and the old, many of whom
were unable to travel. Before they left, the army tore down the walls of the city, then
threatened to slaughter any citizens attempting to rebuild. So, the citizens fearful of their
lives decided to obey the Seekers words, and left the city as it was.
 
Now that the War of the Lance is over, the small number of inhabitants have gone back to 
visiting the small Temple of Majere, but it has been mostly left alone. Only the old
remember what it used to be like in their glory years. The kids seem to find it as just
another area to play. I suppose the city would have continued this way for years, if it were
not for a new proprietor of the city, one who calls himself Lord Kotoasa Sahaluin.
 
Just recently has Lord Kotoasa taken to rebuilding the city now that the fear of the
Seekers has long passed. The walls of the city has been rebuilt to its former strength, and
a large gate now stands in place where an open hole once was. Typically, the proprietor 
charges an entrance fee to the city, in hopes of gathering more funds to assist in the
rebuilding project.
 
One day, not long ago, while in a meeting with the proprietor, there seemed to be an odd
attack upon the city by a large Troll named, Bolgar. At the initial onslaught, the guards
fired wildly at the beast, and it appeared to be slain before the Lords eyes. Having noticed
this, Lord Kotoasa was furious. Not only did his wrath extend to verbal abuse of the
guards, but his strength was enough to raise the slain troll back to life. Whether Lord
Kotoasa has some deep hidden power, and this was a mere display, or some sort of
trickery, it is yet to be seen.  The young men who guard the city appear to do so more out
of fear of Kotoasa then anything else. Though, it is hard to say without further
monitoring. Believe this though, the city of Dart is being rebuilt, and there is something at
work there. Dart will once again be a place for people to come and see in the near future
if the proprietor can keep up at the pace he is going.
 
