Text
Its true, its all true.  Your life does flash before your eyes right
before your death.  In the well over two centuries of my existence that I
lived, I only really have two comments about it.  The first and most obvious
one was, I spent way too much time in my own solitude.  The second one,
well, lets just say I slept way too much.  As my spirit left my body, I
watched.  I watched as the note that I wrote fluttered to the ground as my
body was consumed by the fire and dark energy that was raveled into my
existence quickly burnt my malformed body in to nothing but a pile of black
ash.  Sadly it did not, as I hoped, end there.  As I previously stated, its
true.  The dark queen was not pleased with me and the life I chose to live. 
Maybe, just maybe, if I followed my darker side I would not be in what is
possibly a position thats worse than my previous one.  From creation, I was
an outcast.  My scales were none of the colors of my usual brethren.  I was
not the size of the brothers that fly, yet I had wings that allowed me to
glide along the currents of the wind.  Looking back, I cant help but think,
maybe its right that it ends this way.  The only ones that understood me are
now dead.  I saw my new friend, my brother, and even the one that I wished
to pair with die and turn to stone.  Maybe if I went there before he made
the fatal decision things would be different.  Maybe he was Lucky.  Maybe
Takhisis herself will choose him to guard her in his next incarnation.  My
previous friend, a dark assassin devoted to Chemosh, took his own life years
ago.  Perhaps now, in death, he found the Solace he was looking for.  Now I
am finding out, like my brother did, that, apparently we are not allowed to
leave this plain of existence.  I will not be rocked in Takhisiss arms in
the darkness of the abyss like I hoped.  I will not be brought up to bow
before the gods of light for my good deeds.  Instead, it would appear that I
am being punished.  Punished for what, sadly, I am not aware, but punished
nonetheless.  As my eyes caught the note lying beside the pile of ash that
was once my now outcast form, I quickly glanced at it, wondering what my
next would be.  To who finds me: My name was Nicka, I was a cleric.  I was a
draconian.  Those that I assisted I wish you well.  Those of you that
despised me, may the gods have mercy on your souls and grant you a
punishment fit for your insolence.  The darkness has come, and I cannot join
it, nor can I fight against it.  For me, this was the best decision that I
could make.  Since I could do neither both because of the dark magic that
bonded me, and my heart that did not feel as my brothers did.  I decided to
choose to do neither.  It is both my fault, and the fault of the gods that
my life has came to an end here.  Myself, because I did not follow the
obvious instincts that were weaved into the black magic that was my soul and
existence and the gods, because not a one has showed themselves to me.  Not
even the dark queen herself, who, correct me if I am wrong, but, I was
created to serve anyways?  Do you know what its like to have power - immense
power.  The power to harm, the power to heal, and not have a god to follow? 
For a clerical being like myself, it is, insanity.  And I I choose to end my
madness.  
May the dark gods and the gods of the light do with me as they see fit.
My name was Nicka.
And I was, a cleric.
~
