Rays of Lunitari shone down this night, flashing through the windows with it's red brilliance, the sight of blood being hidden within it's mass.  Though hidden it's bitter smell still remained, letting a nauseous feeling cloud over the half-elf sitting here.  At the table before him was a meal fully prepared, candle lights still burning bright, a shame it all went to waste he thought.
 
Trudging down the stairs to his right came a rather large man, fat bursting out of his suit of plate mail.  With a wry grin he asks, "Tinassil, what shall we do with the bodies?"
 
"Hang them from the tree outside and burn the house.  Let it be lesson to all among Solace, submit to the Queen or fall to death."
 
The large man nods and begins to turn, but stops abruplty, "Do we loot the house?  These people have no need for there wealth in the afterlife."
 
"We take nothing, we are not thieves!  Lord Theriss ordered us to kill all who stood in the way, not ransack the place!"
 
With a frown the large man nodded and trudged back up the stairs.  Returning moments later two men followed behind, all three holding a corpse in hand.  The first held a man, the second a woman and the third a small child, looking to be only 14 summers old.
 
Standing from his seat Tinassil began walking to the front door, speaking as he walked.  "Do the same with any who stand in our way."
 
An hour later he sat on his mount, the house infront of him blazing wildly.  The three bodies hung from the tree near the house, swaying in the wind...-
