Subject The Siren Song~
Text
The sound of heavy boots upon the ship's deck awakens Talorin, the halfling groggily rubbing his eyes. He wrinkles his nose, the strange odor settling into the darkened corner that he had chosen for his nap.
 
"It smells like a wet minotaur in here..." he wonders aloud, pushing himself up to his feet and fastening his belt a bit tighter. Outside he can hear more and more feet making their way across the ship, moving in quick strides. Silently, he moves to the set of stairs leading to the deck, poking his head out to see the commotion. It is then that he sees the same wizard backing toward the side of the ship and fumbling through pockets.
 
"Hey, it's you!" he exclaims, small hand pointing toward the man. "You disappeared in the tavern before I could introd-" A dirty hand grasps Talorin by the topknot, pulling him to the ground. With a squeal of surprise, he clutches the pirate's arm, digging his nails into flesh. With the grasp loosed just enough, Talorin slips from the grip and scrambles to his feet, producing what to most would be a pen-knife. He holds it securely, eyes darting fervently as he moves to stand nearer the wizard.
 
"Of all the ships, why did THIS one need to be attacked by a bunch of boot-licking, centaur-dung-smelling, greasy-haired pirates!"
 
Retreating quickly and allowing himself enough room, the kender places the knife in a pocket and quickly reaches to his back, loosening his hoopak and holding it firmly. He begins twirling forked stick, a shrill wail emitting from the weapon.
