Subject Simo's travels Pt. 1~
Text
Staring out from the northern gate of Thorbardin, Simo thought back on the last two years. He thought of his time beneath the mountain, staying with Hamar Steelforge and his wife. Holding the dual short swords Hamar had forged for him, Hamars final works, he stepped out into the cool night and headed down the mountainside making his way to Qualinesti.
Two days later, as he approached the edge of the forest, a quiet voice, a voice that carried despite its volume, rang out from just behind the trees in elven, "{GTurn back human. Your kind are not welcome in this forest.{x"
Not one for volume, Simo whispered, also in elven, "{bI am no human, and by your accent, you are not of the Qualinesti, so you are as unwelcome as I. Stand aside.{x"
A lithe elf dropped from the trees, clad only in a loincloth and holding a thick stick, carved with images of an elven woman and a unicorn. "{GI protect the forest, not the inhabitants. Humans bring destruction, Ill not have you in this forest.{x"
Simo, straightening, sheathed his dual swords into their single sheath, "{bIve no intention to harm this forest or any of its inhabitants, again I say, stand aside.{x"
"{GI am Sillva Aspenbranch, protector of this forest. You shame your elven blood. Prepare to die.{x"
************************************************************
As Simo cleaned Sillvas blood off his blades, he marveled at Hamars ability in the forge. He passed through the forest without further incident, staying close to the eastern edge, making his way to Solace. -{bI should visit Kaitlin, It has been two years since I last saw her,{x- he thought as he snuck through the borders of the forest.
Four days later, as he cleared the forest, he came upon a man lying on a rock, apparently asleep. Having no quarrel with the man, he snuck past, only to freeze at the words, "{dFor an elf, you sure make a lot of noise.{x"
Simo whirled around to face the man, swords drawn, sizing up his opponent. The man stood near 6 feet tall, and his mohawk must have added another foot on top of that. The swords strapped all over his body glinted in the sunlight, no two the same. His heavily muscled torso was bare, save a buckler on his right shoulder, and a tattoo of an intertwining rose and lily around an axe on his left.
"{dSay now, those are pretty fancy swords you got there, custom job? I dont suppose youd part with them?{x" the man said, holding out a sack of coins.
Simo, silent, shook his head and tightened his grip on the blades.
"{dNo matter, Im taking the swords either way, I was just giving you a sporting chance to walk out of here,{x" said the man, drawing an incredibly long, almost spear-like sword from behind his back.
Simo crouched into a battle stance, prepared for the coming fight. The man yelled, "{dJust remember, I gave you a chance elf!{x" With that, he lunged forward, thrusting the long blade directly at Simo. But Simo saw It coming, he deftly slipped to the left to avoid the long blade and raised his own sword, preparing to attack. Before he had a chance, the man dropped his left hand from the sword, reached up, and plunged a knife, concealed in the buckler, into Simos abdomen.
Simo fell to the ground, dropped his blades, and clutched his wound, trying to stem the flow of blood. The fight was over as quickly as it had begun. The strange man picked up the swords, looking at them fondly, "{dYoure not worthy of beauties like these. Here I wouldnt want to leave you weaponless, even if you are a deadman.{x"
With that, he dropped the knife he had just stabbed Simo with in the dirt in front of him. He crouched down, grinning cruelly in the face of the defeated half-elf, "{dNames Mariek. If you survive this and want your swords back, come find me, prove your worth.{x" As Simo lapsed into unconsciousness, the last thing he remembered was the grinning face of the man.
~
