Moans and cries of anger erupted from the Army of Slaves, their obvious unwant for the storm befalling them.
"{rWhy must the Maelstrom choose to exact her fury at a time like this.{y" The grey figure whispered to himself as rain and harsh winds seemed to furiously attack him. He no longer chose to keep his voice silenced, considering the storms muffling powers. "{rAlthough, maybe the Dark Divine does such for a reason, to guide me perhaps.{y" A sinister chuckle soon follows the last set of words as the grey figure realizes no such thing would happen to the likes of him.
The grey figure snuck onward, pausing at random intervals as troupes of skeletal warriors patrolled the area. His caution was great while he walked among the army of the dead, for he knew the massive numbers against only he would be his downfall. He did not fear the army, but he wasn't dumb either, he refused to try and do something he knew he couldn't accomplish. He continued onward until his journey finally led him to the entrance to the Caverns of the Undead.
