Once he knew for sure that he was safe, he made his way through the open pathway, into the Caverns of Death.He climbed over the sideways tree, and pushed twigs and branches from his path as he shimmied through the created pathway, onward into the caverns. But when he fell to the ground, his feet landing gracefully, and without a sound, his eyes fell upon a skeletal warrior, standing before him, sword in hand, an evil grin upon his face.
A dark, cold whisper emanated from the skeletal beings mouth, barely detectable because of the echo of the winds from the storm outside. "{DWhhhyyyy, do you come here Wretch, of the living{y?" The skeleton cried as his skull moved upward and downward as he inspected the grey figure before him.
"{rI bear a message, it is from H'rar{y." The grey figure replied, his own sinister voice reverberating off the damp, dripping walls of the cavern. Even the skeletal being, upon hearing the voice, had a chill course through it, even with his workings of death, and pure evil, fear gripped him when the figure spoke. Although fear gripped the skeleton, it served Aeleth to the fullest, "{DWhat, messsssssssage is that{y?"
The grey figure did not utter a word, he merely once more flicked his hand and the intestine reacted to his bidding. It shot forward, and wrapped itself around the skeletal warrior's neck. Upon doing so, the figure refused to allow the warrior to act, and he yanked the intestine with a burst of strength flowing through his muscles, allowing the skeletal being to dismember easily.
The skeletal figure fell to the cavern floors with a loud thud that reverberated through the caverns, and a loud clang as it's sword landed upon one of the bones. The skull still spoke, even in it's current form, "{DYou think you can stop ussssss?{y" The skull now grew louder as anger flowed through it, "{DWE ARE DEATH'S ARMY, WE CANNOT BE DEFEATED!!!{y"
