Blood trickled down into her red eyes, forming a pool welling up and spilling over her
coarse and rough skin, dribbling down her cheeks to cradle in the corner of her mouth, bringing
the taste of blood to her senses, arousing the stupor from which the Minotaur dwelled. Her mind reeled
bringing back reality as sharp as the sensation pounding in her skull, her thoughts and motion slowly
forming a cohesive reality.
 
"By Sargas I'll kill them all!" Emmalene roared, disoriented and dazed, still not sure of reality or
what she faced. As her eyes slowly focused, she shook her head and instantly regretted the action, 
it felt like an army had trodden on her skull on the way to battle.... and then the way back.
 
She didn't mind the taste of blood, it was bringing back more memories than the pain was, and
Emmalene quickly found herself ready to eject the bile from her stomach and the sensation of spinning
would not subside.  Poison was playing a part in this no doubt, but it isn't what put her in this situation to start.
No. It was all returning now, too quickly for comfort as once again she was forced to purge her gut until
nothing remained.
The wager had been a simple one.  Too simple, and she had been winning... such a fool. 
Her travels often took her far, and she had, if any Minotaur would call it that, a weakness for gambling.
A puny bunch of humans too rich for their own good, from Neraka, spent many hours priming her for this, their goal.
 
Amongst her people, Emmalene's bloodline was well known for its fine craftsmanship.  There were a fair share whom 
were warriors, and even a champion amongst them in recent generations, but Ss'ssinring bloodline shone
when it came to Smithing.  Many a moon had been spent negotating with outsiders keen to own a weapon
or breastplate bearing their family seal. Legend had it that Mentarn the Great, legendary forefather of their bloodline
had perfected his craftsmanship to make weapons that could face the harshest of conditions, and remain
true to their construction and quality. Unbreakable, it was said. Not so the will of the youngest of their
legacy, it would seem.
Many told Emmalene it was folly to mix business with pleasure, when it came to dealing with the humans, even
those who served the Dark Queen... Now she would come to believe that not all humans were as stupid as
she wanted to believe.
 
The drinks flowed as the wagers increased, Emmalene's luck never running on dry, like the dark meads and spirits
that flowed like winter rains. She could'nt believe her luck, or shouldnt have.  Twenty drinks later, and
a fat pile of steel in front of her, she was ready to end this victory over human stupidity.... And the world
crashed around engulfing her in darkness and pain as blow after blow rained down as she fell under the stupor 
of the chemicals.
"You, cow! Behave or I'll throw you overboard before we reach Palanthas" A surprisingly weak looking human 
yelled.
 
"P..Palanthas?? What is this!? 
Emmalene tried to comprehend just what fate would bring... The holy city!
"I warned you" the frail man said, and with that the world crashed down once more. gulls cried their greedy
moans as waves stuck time and again over the bow. She could not resist the black.
