"Where...what is this place?"  Emmalene felt lost and the instant urge to move, which was a fruitless task as heavy manacles shackled her fast to the spot in which she rest. 
"Have I finally died? Is this the Abyss?" the thought sending shivers down her spine.
a voice replied "No, although the image is of your own doing, not mine"
Emmalene turned every direction she could, trying to pinpoint the location of this voice.
 
A Dark robed figure made its way from the shadows in her mind, midnight coloured emblems adorning the silken cloth, holding a key made of gemstone, its craftsmanship ancient and beautiful, held in a skeletal hand. The cowl covering its face allowed no light to illuminate what lay beneath, and she wasn't quite sure that she wanted to see it anyway.
 
"Well, One of Sargas' and so far from home... destined for  the holy city no less! Oh how fate has a sense of humor...and irony" the voice was raspy and all around her.
 
"What manner of trickery is this? Who are you?" Emmalene boomed, "Have I gone completely mad?" 
 
