herself and left the bar. It was no longer day light out, the night swept in 
quickly, and with it, a cool eastwardly breeze. She strolled the streets of 
Palanthas alone that night; her body exhausted, her mind on over drive. 
 
An over abundance of Evil in the land is what had Quen Illumni's devout 
vexed. "Where are all of the followers of good, and light?" she thought to 
herself.  "The evil in Krynn will surely consume it, if it remains to be this 
way."
 
Aiyre paused briefly to assess her surroundings, when at that moment- 
something unexpected happened. A blinding white explosion of light 
nearly sent her sprawling backwards! 
 
When the light subsided, and Aiyre regained her composure, it was clear 
to her that she was no longer in Palanthas. She was now standing in a 
light colored marble courtyard peppered with light blue flowers, "The 
birthplace of all pleasant dreams," Aiyre thought.
 
Then, from behind her, came a soft, sweet and gentle voice, "Greetings, 
my little one."  She turned to see who the beautiful voice belonged to and 
to her suprise and awe, there stood the ever lovely Blue Lady.
 
"Mishakal!" Aiyre gasped, and quickly genuflected out of respect and 
devotion.  Mishakal smiled warmly and placed her hand upon Aiyre's 
shoulder.
 
"I know what troubles you, and you need not worry," said the beautiful 
Goddess as she guided Aiyre to her feet. "You must journey to the town of 
Solanthus, and seek out The Holy Order, from there you will know what to 
do."
 
And then, it was all gone- she was back, alone on the moon lit streets of 
Palanthas. A single tear danced down her cheek, a reminant from the 
Light Bringer's sheer beauty. 
 
"Solanthus it is, to seek out the Holy Order." Aiyre pondered deeply, 
perhaps from there she would be able to find others of  light to join in the
fight against evil, and the preservation of all that is good.
