hour of the day, the Black moon is well and visible in the sky, seemingly casting 
an appreciative black "glow" upon her.  Taking only a moment to churn the 
earth back over the hole to make it no more than a dip in the ground, making 
sure to cover it with the dying weeds and brambles covering the other 
mausoleums and tombs, Zendfrel fades out of existence and steps into the void 
again.
 
   This time she appears in the bedroom of a small house. The trappings of 
the Qualinesti elves can be seen everywhere, from the furniture to the clothes 
hanging about. Laying in a lavishly appointed bed is a middle aged elf, still 
beautiful and graceful as their race tends to stay, and a his lovely younger wife. 
His features, even in sleep, hold a certain hardness to them often reserved for 
the criminal of mind. 
 
   Turning to listen quietly for stirring in the rest of the house, Zendfrel 
waves her hand, and several hidden glyphs glow briefly throughout the 
imparting deafness and mind numbing weariness into the flesh of the elf's 
children and wife.  Then nothing. Zendfrel simply stands there, watching the elf 
sleep for nearly an hour. As the sands of time drizzle away, her features twist 
into a visage that few in this world have ever seen on her face. Hatred, pure 
and utter loathing that would make Takhisis beam with pride to witness 
envelopes her. Soon though, her fist shaking, breath heavy, and nostrils flaring 
as she grinds her teeth , she closes her eyes taking several more minutes to 
compose herself. 
 
   Finally, the glow of the approaching sun just below the horizon warming 
the night sky to a dark crimson, Zendfrel takes action. Summoning a nightmare 
into the room, commanding its silence immediately as it appears, she walks 
forward to brush it's mane. Whispering words forgotten by most, Zendfrel 
takes advantage of a little known feature of the nightmares summoning.  
Named not just for the play on words of the horses horrifying figure, the 
nightmare begins to fade into a phantasmal being and gallops soundlessly and 
slowly, as if through water towards the elf, shrinking as it goes. 
 
   Soon the creature disappears from the material plane all together to run 
through the elf's dreamscape. As it's hooves strike the ground of the poor elf's 
mind they reverberate through it with horrible images to the sound of charging 
horses. For the elf a small half-eleven girl child appears, covered in the blood of 
her parents who's corpses lay behind her she digs, clawing the earth with 
fingernails broken and bleeding as she works through magical compulsion. 
Staring up at the elf with tear streaked eyes which hold no color, only 
blackness, she whispers dark accusation and promises of retribution.
 
   After a few hours of this the elf bolts upright nearly throwing his wife 
from the bed to be greeted by nothing but the warm, cloudless morning sky 
watching him through his bedroom window. His body cold and clammy, sheets 
drenched with sweat he looks down at his hands, seeing for one horrific 
moment blood. Screaming, then wincing and screaming again as his wife slaps 
him angrily at being upset by the sudden movement and scream, the elf jumps 
out of bed and opens his door to the rest of the house, running to check on his 
kids who stare at him with sleepy eyed confusion. 
 
