look.  A single tear runs down his cheek, collecting the ash with it and
leaving a dark stain in its wake as it slides down his face and falls on the
ground next to the corpse.  Like all things here, even the soil starves for
life,dry and devoid of nutrients it instantly absorbs the tear.  He then
drops to one knee,whispering a silent prayer, he closes the blank eyes of
the corpse and closes his fist around a simple symbol of Mishakal it wears. 
Holding it for a moment he unclasps it and puts it in a pocket on the inside
of his breastplate as he stands and wipes the tear stain from his face.  He
looks down for just a moment longer before a mans voice yelling behind him
breaks him from his trance.  He snarls in annoyance and the stench of the
burned flesh he just realizes he can smell and turns to the man approaching,
"What is it Valnor?"  The man stops to catch his breath as he gets to
Arlanthis and gives a strange glance at the burnt body laying behind him as
he barely recognizes the face of a young cleric who died to an arrow wound
on this very mountain many battles ago.  "Im ready for your messag...  I
recognize that body m'lord."  "Yes, our dead are not sacred here.  The very
brothers and sisters who fight alongside us will be fighting against us
after death.  There is no goodness left in this place."  He pauses for a
moment remembering how nervous the young girl was to join the crusaders on
their last raid, and how he soothed her with assurances the gods will watch
over her.  And even after the arrow struck her neck and her life slipped out
her eyes, the gods frowned upon her again and let her corpse be reanimated
and further desecrated.  Arlanthis leans in close to the ear of the corpse
and whispers "Fear not sister, for your tormentors are quick to follow."  He
then kisses the forehead of the woman and turns to the man, "Burn all the
bodies, but burn our fallen brothers and sisters separately from the rest." 
He says this turning and looking out over a massive field of twisted and
burning corpses.  Men throw disfigured corpses and bones into huge pyres
constructed throughout the field.  Mercenaries pick through the remains of
the undead, scavenging rings,clothing, anything of worth from the fallen
clan."  We have purged the undead from the land, our names shall be
remembered and those that have lost their lives in this pursuit.  Send word
to the High Priestess that though im sure we will see a few stragglers that
we missed, for now...  The Dargaard pass is safe."  He then unties the
clasps on his breastplate and lets it fall to the ground.  "You and your men
have done well."  Tossing a bag of coins to the man, "Treat your men tonight
in Solanthus, I will see that they have a warm meal and proper rest."  The
man grins,salutes, then runs back down the mountain side to a large camp
with his mercenarys.  Arlanthis can hear cheering and singing as he turns
and looks out over the land toward the port o call, wind wiping his hair. 
"Your will be done O Sword of Justice.  The wicked reap what they sow."  He
just stands and stares out over the land for quite some time before
returning to his tent.  As he lays his head on his cot and can barely hear a
voice in the back of his head "Only the Knights of Tahkisis remain...." 
Arlanthis lets out a heavy sigh and closes his eyes, drifting into slumber,
already thinking of a declaration to send the black knights.  
