"Again, someone interrupts my solitude."
"But... they're scared too."
"Are you in pain, too?"
"I'm sorry."
 
"The pain is gone.  Gone like a bad dream."
"A nightmare that won't leave me alone."
"But for now I don't hurt."
"I don't hurt except for yet another pain."
"Guilt."
 
 
The sun breaks over a forest canopy.  Rays of light shine on a young woman,
causing her to stir.  Her eyes squint as her mind awakes.  Awoken into warm
