The wind blew gently across the Palanthian night sky.  A young woman
unseen by the naked eye was running at her full speed down an alley.
The night had been eventful, and she was not used to putting forward
this much effort.  She almost stopped in wonder to as if whether or
not she was getting herself into more then she could handle.
 
She came around the corner of the alley, having her question answered
for her.  'Dead end,' came the thought to Melody.  She found herself
staring at three buildings conjoined, making it impossible for the
average person to go any further, with a building height of thirty
feet.  However, she was anyone but average...
 
A bolt whizzed by her head, her eyes catching it only lifesparingly
shorter then its speed, and enough time for her reflexes to kick in.
 
'Neither is he,' She thought, on the topic of average.  She looked
to the top of the building to see the man she was chasing, one leg
ontop of the edge of the building, one arm bent halfway up and bearing
a crossbow, and the wind rippling his cloak gently.  The full moon
of Solinari stood behind him in defiance, and the image of general
finesse this man gave off so naturally pissed her off.  "Fuck you,"
she yelled, frantically started climbing / running up the side
of the building.  He turned, and disappeared as she scaled.
 
Within seconds, Melody pulled herself up to the top of the building,
and straight across from her was her target.  She reached to her
hips, slowly sliding out her daggers as she approached the man.
He had his back to her, but as she approached, he turned around, opening
his arms and stepping up onto the side of the building.
 
"Don't try it this time.  I got your ass, fare and square," Melody snarled
at the man.
 
"This is where the silly games end," said the man, giving the hint of an
accent to Melody.
 
Melody continued to step forward, her muscles tensing and her heart pounding.
She was going to have to make this go down flawless.  She knew, as much
as she hated it, that he was every bit as quick as her.  However, was he
going to read her movements right?
 
"What's the matter?  You scurr'ed?  You ain't got no game, you ain't got no
skill, and you ain't got no talent boy,"  Melody spat out as a taunt.
 
"Boy?"  He said.  She could pick at the tone in his voice; he wasen't amused.
 
"You are quite funny to me," he continued.  He popped the top of a potion
in his hand and downed it, tossing it over his shoulder.  One arm went to
his side, while the other reached out to Melody, beckoning her forward.
 
She charged at him, ready to take her and him plummeting to the ground
to get the bastard.  As she lunged, he jumped back and was... FLYING!?
"Shit, shit, shit, shit, SHIT!"  She yelled, as she found herself unable
to stop, plummeting towards the ground.  *CRACK* she heard clearly from
her left arm as she landed, and pain seared through her.  She looked up
at the man to see him still floating in air.  He lingered for a moment,
and then flew up and away, into the night sky.
 
"Damnit," Melody said.  "Got away..."  She stood up, pain slowly throbbing
to its height in her arm.  She spat at the ground, looking up one more
time, before slinking into the quiet of the night.
