were everywhere; hung over the cha irs, on the floor with fearful looks,
there was even one on burnt onto the roof of the cabin.  On the floor in
front of the entrance to the cabin was a nicely sized white circle
imprinted.  Walking to the nearest town, he had asked what happened to the
group.  The citizens were happy to tell the tale of the group, who had
bullied the citizens in the past.  White robes of the Orders of High Sorcery
came into town one day, heard the stories of the malicious group, and went
to the cabin to confront them.  The rest was a mystery to the citizens, but
the effect was immediate on Fyrah, all his hatred and vengeance drained from
his body, and was replaced by respect for the cause of protecting others. 
He thought, If he could use his strength to prevent others the heartache
that he had endured, all while protecting magic which he has come to
respect, what higher honor could he have?  Researching and finding the
shrine of Solinari, the diety of the white robes, he devoted his life to the
cause.  Being marked, Fyrah stood up and left the shrine, ready to set out
