The hammock that hangs outside of the Healer's Hut creaks softly as it sways
to and fro. The kagonesti that rests in it breathes a soft sigh, longing for
the young boy who usually accompanies her here. In the absence of his
presence, though, she forces her mind to travel in a different direction.
With a sigh, she sits up and moves to her bag, which sits in its own alcove,
within the Healer's Hut. The elder druid is absent, allowing Silvaria's
thoughts to be focused on the roll of paper she pulls from the bag. It is
weathered, but she had expected that. There is little she can do to protect
such things from the elements here.
 
Unrolling the paper reveals a floorplan that she considers carefully. The
floor of the Healer's Hut is soil, but it is packed down hard by the amount
of people who move through it by day and by night. She spreads this roll of
paper out and pulls out a pen and a pot of black ink from her bag.
 
'{CPerhaps... I can find someone who can make instruments...{X' she thinks
aloud, adding the thought underneath a note that marks where a Temple to
Branchala might go. '{C...And here... Where Druids can come to train their
skills... I will need to speak again with Amon...{X' she mutters. '{CThe
Main Hall of the Temple ought to be in a tree... an enormous tree. Where
better to be reverent of the Cycle than in then embrace of one of Her
most cherished creatures...?{X'
 
Silvaria's work on the floorplan continues well through the day,
regardless of those who walk through the Healer's Hut. It is only once
nighttime has fallen, and she can no longer work by the light of the day
that Silvaria finally rolls up the sheet of paper and stashes it back in
her bag. '{C...It will be beautiful...{X' she murmurs aloud.
 
'{yWhat will?{X' The familiar voice of Golametti calls out to her, and so
deeply in her thoughts she had withdrawn, she is startled by it.
 
'{COh. The new Temple, of course,{X' she states, touching her hand to
her heart and chuckling at the elderly druid.
 
Golametti lifts a bushy eyebrow at her, seemingly skeptical. '{y"New"
Temple? What's wrong with -this- Temple, hmmm?{x'
 
Silvaria tilts her head and sighs. '{CNothing is -wrong- with it,
Golametti... But I want to expand upon the beauty here. I want it to be
more of a haven -- and roomier, so we don't feel so cramped.{X'
 
'{y...I think you ought to talk to more people before you start making
such big changes, young one. But, who am I? Just a cranky old druid...
I heard you mumbling about trees over there -- I want my house to stay
right where it is, you hear??{x' he rambles, mumbling to himself in the
Kagonesti tongue as he meanders into his private area of the Hut.
 
Silvaria just shakes her head, grinning slightly after him. She
sighs and tucks her bag into its alcove, before stepping outside of the
Hut and making a soft, hooting call -- then listening close to see if
it is returned.
~
