Heavy clouds hung overhead in the dark night sky, a storm on the brink. Casual 
winds wisps quietly through the small city, bits of leaves flowing through 
the city, trailing from the forest nearby. The animals knew a storm was coming, 
sort of like a special sense. Not a sound could be heard within the city, or forest.
 
A citadel stood tall amongst the small area. South through Vingaard forest, a 
small ways away from the great city of Palanthas, a draconian citadel stood. 
Unknown to many, but revered by few, the citadel stood quietly in the night. 
The normal activity of the draconians were not as usual, in fact... None could be seen.
Deep within the quiet citadel, down many passages and corridors, was a dark room.
Within this room, that seemed darker than every other room amongst the citadel, 
an odd smell arose. The smell wasn't necessarily bad, nor was it good. It didn't 
carry the sweet smell of flowers that could be found within the forest up north 
nor did it carry the smell of death. The smell was just...Different.
Within this odd room was one single light. It did not burn bright, illuminating 
the darkness as it should, but lit just a small corner of the room. However
faint it was, it did reveal an altar. An altar of utmost evil, and built of
obsidian, was erected here for the Dark Queen, Takhisis.
Nearby this obsidian altar, stood two figures, shrouded in the darkness of the room.
The silence, was finally broken as one of the men spoke. A tall, grey cloaked
man stood tall, his eyes opening after who knows how long, "{dI have heard Her words.{X"
The man seemed to be speaking to the other figure that was present.
"{rGood, it has been many hours since you last spoke.{X" The other figure spoke
in reply to the first. The second figure, stepped forward to bring himself
closer to the hooded figure. "{rWhat did she say?{X"
"{dMany hours to you, are mere minutes within Her domain.{X" A raspy reply
is what the hooded figure can offer, his throat dry and cracking, the price
of not speaking, eating, or drinking for many hours. "{dI prayed unto Her,
and she answered.{X" He continued, his voice slowly returning to its normal
sound, "{dWe must go to Santion.{X"
"{rWhy there?{X" The other man asks, his voice bouncing off the short walls
of the dark room, a mild echo occuring.
"{dDo not ask question, Jerrid. It is Her will, and it -must- be done.{X"
"{rThen let's be on our way.{X" Jerrid replies, stepping closer to the altar
a final time before they set upon their journey. As the man steps toward the altar,
to pray, the small light illuminates some of his features. No helm is atop
his head, though he is adorned in armor. Jet black hair, the color of the night
sky falls messily down his head, his shoulders where it stops. His eyes, are
of the deepest of greys, the color of a deep morning fog. They are like a
reflective piece of steel, hiding his soul beneath. Obsidian colored armor
is his adornment, giving way that he is a warrior. Though large and muscular,
standing at a full height of six foot six inches, he is not unharmed. Numerous
cuts and scars align the mans throat, memories of past battles within each.
Unsheathing his blade, with an evil grin, the Knight kneels before the altar.
The obsidian sword swiftly, and with precision, raises in the air as he prays
to the Dark Queen. "{BMay you watch over us on our journey, M'lady.{X"
And with that, the pair set out into the cold, windy night, a long journey
ahead, but with purpose.
~
