The streets of Palanthas had grown quiet in recent months. Law and order had been 
hard fought and won by the efforts of the Crown's favorite knights, and the lawless 
factions that once ruled the streets were now scarcely recognized or feared by the 
populace. It was a calm day, with an overcast sun setting on the horizon, casting off 
amber rays and diffusing the surrounding sky in an attractive red hue.
 
Jafrod was an honest man. He grew up on the now relatively calm street of Smith's 
Alley. Long ago, the Alley was a dangerous part of the city, filled with criminals of all 
factions, races, and sizes. Now peasants leisurely hung their laundry out on the 
lines, smiling and waving as patrols would pass by on adjacent blocks. Jafrod was 
outside his small home on the Alley, scrubbing the dirt off of his facade when he 
heard the first oddity of the day.
 
"Stop that man! Help! Guards!" The shouting was coming from down the street off 
Temple Row. Jafrod put down his rag and straightened himself up to full height. He 
raised an eyebrow and looked in the direction of the shouting. He waited a few 
moments, but no one came running down the Alley as he had expected. Dismissing 
it as a fence getting caught at one of the shops on Temple Row, Jafrod stooped 
down again to resume his chore of cleaning.
 
Jafrod *hated* the simplicity of his life, and more importantly, he *hated* cleaning 
the facade of his home. However, that is what he did, and what he was doing when 
the second oddity of that day occurred to him.
 
Two knights, wearing bright shining armor, carrying ancient halberds marched down 
the Alley, never glancing or acknowledging the peasants that began to assemble in 
front of their homes to see what was going on. Their feet moved in near perfect 
unison, a disciplined march that could only come from the years of training that 
accompany a full ranking Solamnic Officer. These particular knights came from the 
customs post at the docks in the north of the city.
 
The pair stopped, and turned to face Jafrod. Both men had long flowing mustaches, 
and nearly looked identical, the one defining trait between them being the color of 
their mustaches. The man on Jafrod's left had a red mustache, while the one on his 
right wore a dirty blonde. 
 
The "red" knight spoke first :
 
"Citizen of Palanthas, state your name clearly". Jafrod's heart sank into his stomach.
What could these men possibly want?
 
"Uh.. J..Jafrod Bensson sir"
 
Then the blonde knight spoke, "Jafrod Bensson, by order of the Crown your home is 
to be searched for contraband, if you do not comply with this order and grant us 
entry you shall be arrested under the charge of Obstruction of an Official 
Investigation. Do you understand my directive peasant?"
 
Jafrod's stomach turned itself into a knot. Somewhere deep down in his soul, he felt 
a spark, a tiny, miniscule sliver of anger and hatred at this pompous knight and his 
Rule of Law, and he finally responded to the knights,
 
"Yes m'lords, please, enter my home, and search as you like."
 
The knights immediately entered the humble home, barely waiting for him to finish 
accepting their demands. Inside they found little of interest, food stores, a straw 
mattress, dirty walls. The knights rummaged through what little posessions Jafrod 
had, never speaking a word. After about 15 minutes of searching, they exchanged a 
glance with each other, and nodded slowly to each other.
 
"Peasant, Jafrod Bensson" the red knight spoke.
 
"Y-yes sir."
 
"Your home clearly contains no contraband, the Crown thanks you for your compliance"
 
Then the blonde knight added "If you see any strange activity tonight, please report it 
to the City Guard immediately. We are looking for a box containing very dangerous 
contraband, it cleared customs at the port this morning and was marked to be 
delivered to this address." His expression softened a little as he continued, "When 
we discovered our folly in clearing the box we thought you might have already 
received it. Clearly you know nothing of this item."
 
Jafrod was taken aback. Why would a box of contraband be sent to him? Who sent 
it? What contraband was so important that 2 high ranking knights would march 
halfway across the city in search of it?
 
More and more questions raced through his head as he wondered if he were in 
danger. The knights finally excused themselves politely, making Jafrod feel that they 
maybe weren't the pompous jackasses who demanded their way into his home after 
all. As soon as he saw them clear the Alley and disappear off to the south, he 
rushed back inside his home and bolted the door.
